===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|yi|נודניק}} < root of {{m|yi|נודיען||to bore}} + {{m|yi|־ניק||noun-forming suffix}} (English {{m|en|-nik}}). Ultimately from {{der|en|sla-pro|*nuda}} < {{der|en|ine-pro|*newti-||need}} < {{m|ine-pro|*new-||death, to be exhausted}}.

Compare {{cog|ru|ну́дный||tedious}}, {{cog|uk|ну́дний||tedious}}, {{cog|pl|nudny||boring}}, {{cog|sk|nudný||boring}}, {{cog|cu|ноудити}} or {{m|cu|нѫдити||to compel}}, {{cog|he|נוּדְנִיק||[[nag#Verb|nag]]}}.

